# Zapret Hub

Desktop application scaffold for Windows that manages external network utilities,
configuration packs, updates, diagnostics, logs, and mod overlays from one UI.

## Stack

- Python 3.11+
- PySide6 desktop UI
- Modular backend services
- PyInstaller packaging for `.exe`

## Run in development

```powershell
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
pip install -e .[dev]
python -m zapret_hub.main
```

## Build `.exe`

```powershell
pyinstaller packaging\zapret_hub.spec
```

## Architecture

- `src/zapret_hub/app.py`: desktop app entry and Qt bootstrap
- `src/zapret_hub/bootstrap.py`: application context and service wiring
- `src/zapret_hub/domain/`: core entities from the technical specification
- `src/zapret_hub/services/`: backend managers for settings, storage, logging, processes, merge, mods, updates, diagnostics
- `src/zapret_hub/ui/`: modern desktop shell and theming

## Current MVP scaffold

- Main window with sections: home, components, mods, diagnostics, logs, updates, settings
- Start and stop of active components through one UI
- Separated runtime folders: `configs`, `mods`, `merged_runtime`, `backups`, `logs`, `data`, `cache`
- Persistent settings via JSON
- Mod index loading from JSON cache and local install workflow
- Safe merged config rebuild with backup before rebuild
- Diagnostics and log viewer

## Next recommended steps

- Replace sample component commands with real external utilities and launch adapters
- Implement Windows autostart, tray mode, and background lifecycle handling
- Add async workers for long operations and progress reporting
- Add file editor, diff viewer, and advanced or expert settings
- Connect real remote update feeds and mod package downloads
